HEADWORD: ISKCON
<hw>ISKCON</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[acronym from The
<ets>I</ets>nternational <ets>S</ets>ociety for <ets>K</ets>rishna
<ets>Con</ets>sciousness.]</ety> <def>The abbreviation for International
Society for Krishna Consciousness, a society founded in the US in 1966;
based on Vedic scriptures. Groups of devotees engage in joyful chanting
of "Hare Krishna" ("O Krishna!").</def> <mark>[acronym]</mark> ⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> Hare Krishna, International Society for Krishna
Consciousness, the Hare Krishnas.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

